    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Reaching Back in Time</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ken Grunstra letter observes that if scientists in the future had found a way to signal back in time we would have heard from them by now (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It seems obvious to me that scientists in the future will never find a way to signal back in time, described in ''Faster Than Light, Maybe, but Not Back to the Future'' (May 30). If they were to do so, wouldn't we have heard from them by now?</p>
        <p>KEN GRUNSTRA  Santa Cruz, Calif.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
